{"ts": "2026-06-09T16:45:55.788361+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "| MCP:0TXOiM | successfully downloaded text file (SHA: ce907a77bdc824b30f8d9cc6bce388af0342e3fe)", "id": "lc_95c2c921-71b1-448e-a41e-b5356c56864c"}, {"type": "text", "text": "| MCP:0TXOiM | import { useEffect } from \"react\";\n| MCP:0TXOiM | import Logout from \"../components/auth/Logout\";\n| MCP:0TXOiM | import Center from \"../components/utils/Center\";\n| MCP:0TXOiM | \n| MCP:0TXOiM | const Home = (props) => {\n| MCP:0TXOiM |   useEffect(() => {}, []); // eslint-disable-line react-hooks/exhaustive-deps\n| MCP:0TXOiM | \n| MCP:0TXOiM |   return (\n| MCP:0TXOiM |     <Center>\n| MCP:0TXOiM |       <Logout />\n| MCP:0TXOiM |     </Center>\n| MCP:0TXOiM |   );\n| MCP:0TXOiM | };\n| MCP:0TXOiM | \n| MCP:0TXOiM | export default Home;", "id": "lc_21fcb99b-84e6-4acd-b183-0df7c7b22763"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "6fd2f50e-90a5-47a9-9b37-63c52357046a", "tool_call_id": "call_c157a417336d480d93f9168a", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-09T16:45:55.788789+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "| MCP:0TXOiM | successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 2c9591d86784fe512916174841794167655d2695)", "id": "lc_004e77bd-782c-48c0-9494-ef949914e767"}, {"type": "text", "text": "| MCP:0TXOiM | import { initializeApp } from \"firebase/app\";\n| MCP:0TXOiM | import { firebaseConfig } from \"./firebase.config\";\n| MCP:0TXOiM | import { getAuth, GoogleAuthProvider } from \"firebase/auth\";\n| MCP:0TXOiM | \n| MCP:0TXOiM | export const Firebase = initializeApp(firebaseConfig);\n| MCP:0TXOiM | export const auth = getAuth();\n| MCP:0TXOiM | export const Providers = { google: new GoogleAuthProvider() };", "id": "lc_f31aa081-05a5-448d-ac47-e7d1b25c0ddf"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "e63e5e96-2eaf-4971-9da0-f55812eaa398", "tool_call_id": "call_63fcaf4400744528be18be87", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-09T16:46:09.144619+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Here's how routing is configured in this starter and which routes require authentication:\n\n## Routing Architecture\n\nThis is a **React Router v6** application that uses a **centralized route configuration** pattern with **Firebase authentication**.\n\n### How It Works\n\n1. **Route Definitions** (`src/config/routes.js`):\n   Routes are defined as an array of objects, each with:\n   - `path` – the URL path\n   - `component` – the React component to render\n   - `name` – a human-readable label\n   - `protected` – a **boolean flag** indicating whether the route requires authentication\n\n2. **Route Rendering** (`src/App.js`):\n   The `App` component maps over the routes array and conditionally wraps protected routes with an `<AuthChecker>` component:\n   ```jsx\n   route.protected ? (\n     <AuthChecker><route.component /></AuthChecker>\n   ) : (\n     <route.component />\n   )\n   ```\n\n3. **Authentication Guard** (`src/components/auth/AuthChecker.js`):\n   If no authenticated user exists (`!auth.currentUser`), it immediately **redirects to `/login`** using React Router's `useNavigate`.\n\n---\n\n### The Two Routes\n\n| Path | Component | `protected` | Status |\n|------|-----------|-------------|--------|\n| `\"\"` (root `/`) | `Home` | **`true`** | 🔒 **Requires authentication** |\n| `/login` | `Login` | **`false`** | 🌐 **Public** |\n\n- **Protected (Home page, `/`)**: Displays a `Logout` button. If an unauthenticated user tries to access it, the `AuthChecker` wrapper redirects them to `/login`.\n- **Public (Login screen, `/login`)**: Uses Firebase's `GoogleAuthProvider` for Google sign-in. Accessible to anyone regardless of auth state.\n\n### Bootstrap Flow\n1. On app load, `auth.onAuthStateChanged()` listens for Firebase auth state changes.\n2. While waiting, a loading spinner is shown.\n3. Once the auth state resolves, routes are rendered with the protected/public logic applied.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 462, "prompt_tokens": 8051, "total_tokens": 8513, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 16, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 7424}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "mimo-v2.5-pro", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "4d66adf69e624641bd66614961e11265", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ead46-c0ce-7bd2-8082-c71cae5d75ba-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 8051, "output_tokens": 462, "total_tokens": 8513, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 7424}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 16}}}}]}}}
